ZH: 他决定弃权，不参加这次选举。
EN: He decided to abstain and not participate in this election.

ZH: 在关键时刻，她选择了弃权，让别人做决定。
EN: At a critical moment, she chose to abstain and let others make the decision.

ZH: 弃权是一种表明不同意的方式。
EN: Abstaining is a way to show disagreement.

ZH: 他的意见与大家不同，因此他选择了弃权。
EN: His opinion was different from everyone else's, so he chose to abstain.

ZH: 对于这个问题，我还没有决定是否弃权。
EN: I haven't decided yet whether to abstain on this issue.

ZH: 弃权并不意味着没有意见。
EN: Abstaining doesn't mean having no opinion.

ZH: 弃权可以是一种政治抗议的方式。
EN: Abstaining can be a form of political protest.

ZH: 在这个投票中，有五人弃权。
EN: Five people abstained in this vote.

ZH: 怀疑这次选举是否公平，许多人选择弃权。
EN: Doubting the fairness of this election, many people chose to abstain.

ZH: 弃权也可以是一种保持中立的方式。
EN: Abstaining can also be a way to remain neutral.

ZH: 她决定弃权，因为她觉得自己不够了解这个问题。
EN: She decided to abstain because she felt she didn't know enough about the issue.

ZH: 弃权需要勇气，因为这意味着站在少数人的一边。
EN: Abstaining takes courage because it means standing on the side of the minority.

ZH: 对于这个问题，大家分成了两个阵营，只有少数人选择弃权。
EN: People were divided into two camps on this issue, and only a few chose to abstain.

ZH: 弃权在一些情况下可以改变整个结果。
EN: Abstaining can change the entire outcome in some cases.

ZH: 他害怕做出错误的决定，所以选择了弃权。
EN: He was afraid of making the wrong decision, so he chose to abstain.

ZH: 这次投票有很多人弃权，导致了投票结果的不确定性。
EN: There were many abstentions in this vote, leading to uncertainty in the outcome.

